    <edge source="Hist, a Native American woman and betrothed of Chingachgook, took several measures to convince Judith and Hetty to seek refuge in the Ark. She showed herself in the stern of the scow and made many gestures and signs, attempting to indicate that the girls should make a circuit to avoid the Castle and approach the Ark from the eastward. However, these signs were distrusted or misunderstood by Judith.&#10;&#10;There could be several reasons why Hist's signs were not trusted or understood. One possibility is that Judith was not yet sufficiently aware of the real state of things to put full confidence in either party, and therefore she may have been hesitant to follow Hist's directions. Additionally, it is mentioned that Judith kept more aloof and paddled slowly back to the north, where she could command the widest view and have the fairest field for flight before her. This suggests that Judith may have been prioritizing her own safety and desire for a clear escape route over Hist's instructions.&#10;&#10;Another possibility is that there was a language barrier or cultural misunderstanding at play. While Hist is a Native American woman, Judith and Hetty are European-American, and it's possible that they had difficulty understanding Hist's gestures or that there were cultural differences in communication styles. Ultimately, the reason for the misunderstanding is not explicitly stated in the narrative, but it is clear that Hist's attempts to communicate with Judith and Hetty were unsuccessful." target="The urgent circumstances that compelled Chingachgook to tell Hist to leave the Ark were the intense struggle between Hurry Harry and the three Hurons inside the castle. The combatants were caged, making it almost impossible for anyone to get in or out of the building. Chingachgook, who had all the arms in the Ark, felt at a loss because there was no means of using them or passing them to their owners. He wanted Hist to take the remaining canoe and join Hutter's daughters to save herself and warn them of their danger.&#10;&#10;However, Chingachgook was unable to convince Hist to leave the Ark despite her refusal due to the exigency of the moment, which did not allow for delay. Additionally, Hist, at that moment, could not be persuaded by any human power to quit the Ark, showing her firm determination to stay on board.">
